# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 1️⃣ Error: "require is not defined in ES module scope"
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Occurred in Lambda on Node.js 24.x runtime:
# ReferenceError: require is not defined in ES module scope, you can use import instead
# Stack trace example:
#   at file:///var/task/index.mjs:1:13
# Cause:
# - Node.js 24.x Lambda uses ES Modules
# - Using `const AWS = require('aws-sdk')` is invalid in ES Module
# Resolution:
# - Use ES Module imports:
#   import { DynamoDBClient } from "@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb";
#   import { DynamoDBDocumentClient, ScanCommand, PutCommand } from "@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb";
# - Rename Lambda file extension to `.mjs`
# - Replace require() with import/export

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 2️⃣ Error: "Route not found" in frontend
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Occurred when calling API from HTML /fetch
# Example: fetch(API + "/products")
# Cause:
# - The path in Lambda code used event.resource, which matches API Gateway resource path.
# - Resource paths in API Gateway are case-sensitive and must match exactly
#   e.g., `/Products` vs `/products`
# Resolution:
# - Check resource path in API Gateway exactly
#   - Lambda code should check `/Products` and `/Orders` if those are the resource names
# - Match frontend fetch calls to the same resource path
#   - fetch(API + "/Products") for GET
#   - fetch(API + "/Orders") for POST

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 3️⃣ Error: 403 / CORS errors from frontend
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Occurred when S3 hosted HTML tried to call API Gateway
# Cause:
# - API Gateway did not have CORS enabled
# - Browser blocked cross-origin request
# Resolution:
# - Enable CORS in API Gateway on both /Products and /Orders
#   - Allowed origins: *
#   - Allowed methods: GET, POST
# - Or, configure Lambda proxy response to include headers:
#   headers: { "Access-Control-Allow-Origin": "*" }

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 4️⃣ Error: Lambda invocation fails silently (Init Error)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Example log:
#   INIT_REPORT Init Duration: 314.86 ms Phase: init Status: error
#   Error Type: Runtime.Unknown
# Cause:
# - Lambda function code invalid (require used in ES Module)
# - Missing dependencies
# Resolution:
# - Fix ES Module imports
# - Ensure node_modules are included if using packages not built-in in Lambda
# - Check Node.js runtime version (24.x) matches ES Module style

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 5️⃣ Error: POST requests fail / no body parsed
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Cause:
# - Lambda event.body is a string by default in Lambda proxy integration
# - Forgot to JSON.parse(event.body)
# Resolution:
# - Parse event body:
#   const body = JSON.parse(event.body);

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 6️⃣ Error: API Gateway Invoke permission denied
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Cause:
# - Lambda did not have a resource policy allowing API Gateway to invoke it
# Resolution:
# - Add permission via CLI:
# aws lambda add-permission --function-name store-api \
#     --statement-id api-gateway-invoke \
#     --action lambda:InvokeFunction \
#     --principal apigateway.amazonaws.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 7️⃣ Error: S3 static website cannot load HTML / JS
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Cause:
# - Bucket had Block Public Access enabled
# - Objects not public
# Resolution:
# - Disable "Block all public access" when creating bucket
# - Add bucket policy for public read:
cat > s3-bucket-policy.json << 'EOF'
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::mini-store-YOURNAME-123/*"
    }
  ]
}
EOF
# - Upload HTML/JS files to S3 bucket
# - Enable Static Website Hosting in S3 bucket properties

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 8️⃣ Error: Node.js local dev confusion (npm / modules)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Cause:
# - You did not have local npm project
# - Tried using @aws-sdk modules without installing them
# Resolution:
# - If using local dev, run:
#   npm init -y
#   npm install @aws-sdk/client-dynamodb @aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb
# - For Lambda deployment without local, AWS Lambda Node.js runtime includes `aws-sdk` built-in

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 9️⃣ Error: Misaligned API Stage / URL
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Cause:
# - Stage Dev URL: https://mslmh8j921.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Dev
# - Frontend fetch call used wrong case or missing stage prefix
# Resolution:
# - Always include stage in URL:
#   fetch("https://mslmh8j921.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Dev/Products")
# - Match resource paths exactly as in API Gateway

# =========================================================
# ✅ Summary of Lessons Learned
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Node.js 24.x Lambda => Use ES Modules (import/export)
# 2. Always match API Gateway resource paths in Lambda and frontend
# 3. CORS must be configured for S3 hosted HTML + API Gateway
# 4. Lambda POST requires JSON.parse(event.body)
# 5. Always deploy API Gateway stage after code/resource changes
# 6. S3 hosting requires public read / static website configuration
# 7. Check CloudWatch logs for detailed Lambda errors
# 8. API Gateway permission needed for Lambda invocation
# =========================================================

